      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the primary QoI; direct mapping to clinical hemolysis threshold documented.",
      "rationale": "The NIH is computed and compared against the clinical threshold. However, the model outputs volume-averaged shear stress as a surrogate for sub-grid hemolysis contributions, introducing a QoI mapping gap. Achieved level 3."
